b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":704,"category_name":"Events","pr_category_id":"4","title_name":"A Raid Event Revival, Skyborne Spectacle, Is Now Live!","message":"<div>Up to four players with four adventurers each (up to 16 adventurers in total!) can battle together in the Skyborne Spectacle raid event revival, which began <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1567231200\\"><\/span>. Take on event-specific quests to defeat the water-attuned raid boss and earn rewards!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/3ad4f173f770e116f48150d16e3aa279.png\\"><\/div><div>The prince and his friends have come to a town that will be celebrating the Lunar New Year. There&#39;ll be food, dragon dances, and even spectacular pyroblossoms at night... But danger arises suddenly amidst preparations for the event! A young practitioner of kung fu, a brave wanderer, and a panda dragon will rise up to face a mighty enemy who&#39;s disrupting the flow of mana!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>An adventurer, Su Fang, will join you during this event. Increase your friendship with him to add him to your roster permanently. You can also collect blazons and emblems to get the dragon Peng Lai and the Dragon Dance wyrmprint.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Find the Skyborne Spectacle raid event revival details below.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Additions<\/div><div>\\u30fbNew difficulty added<\/div><div>A new raid battle difficulty, Nightmare, has been added.<\/div><div>It will unlock if you have completed Valfarre Clash EX.<\/div><div>Nightmare difficulty requires the same amount of otherworld fragments and getherwings as Expert difficulty, and the drop rewards are also the same.<\/div><div>Once per day when you clear Nightmare difficulty, you can get a Grand Bounty.<\/div><div>Note: The Grand Bounty you receive is randomly selected from a set of rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Duration<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1567231200\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1568267999\\"><\/span><\/div><div>\\u30fbIf the event ends while you are in a quest, the quest will continue until the results have been determined. You will be able to earn rewards according to the results of the quest.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Reward Availability Period<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1567231200\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1568872799\\"><\/span><\/div><div>\\u30fbYou will be able to perform blazon summons and obtain emblem rewards during this period.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Temporary Adventurers<\/div><div>When you complete quests, you will increase the friendship with any temporary adventurers in your team. If you maximize your friendship with a temporary adventurer, they will permanently remain in your collection, allowing you to include them in your team after the event ends. Their level, stats, equipment, and position in your team and collection will be maintained.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Note: Even if an event adventurer isn&#39;t permanently added to your collection, any items used to upgrade their level, unlock their mana circles, and promote them will not be returned.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0If Su Fang Previously Joined as a Temporary Adventurer<\/div><div>You can include Su Fang in your team again when this event starts, and he will maintain the same level and stats as when this event was held previously.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Raid Battles<\/div><div>Raid battles are co-op battles where up to four teams (16 adventurers) can cooperate against a raid boss together! There are four difficulty levels available: Beginner, Standard, Expert, and Nightmare.<\/div><div>Raid battles require otherworld fragments and getherwings.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Extra Raid Battles<\/div><div>There is a chance that an Extra Raid Battle will appear for players who clear raid battles on Expert or Nightmare.<\/div><div>The quest will disappear again upon completion.<\/div><div>The quest will reappear when the conditions are met again.<\/div><div>No getherwings or otherworld fragments are required to play extra raid battles.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Blazon Summons<\/div><div>Complete boss battles and raid battles to obtain peregrine blazons. Blazons collected can be used for blazon summoning to get event-specific 5\\u2605 dragons, 4\\u2605 wyrmprints, and other rewards.<\/div><div>After obtaining the dragon Peng Lai through summoning, you can reset the contents available.<\/div><div>From the 5th reset onward, you must accept all rewards before you can reset the contents available.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Emblems<\/div><div>You can obtain event-specific wyrmprints and other rewards based on the total number of emblems you gather during the event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Endeavors<\/div><div>Two types of event endeavors will be available during the event: Daily and Limited.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Castle Stories<\/div><div>A new story has been added to Castle Stories. You can read it by using Looking Glasses, which can be obtained via emblem rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Epilogue<\/div><div>The epilogue for the Skyborne Spectacle raid event revival will unlock <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1568268000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>Note: To view the epilogue, you must complete chapter 6 of the event story.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Epilogue Availability<\/div><div><span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1568268000\\"><\/span> to <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1568872799\\"><\/span><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>1. During raid battles, you will only recover 1\/4 of the amount of HP from certain skills and abilities.<\/div><div>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate in event quests.<\/div><div>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.<\/div><div>4. If you do not maximize your friendship with temporary adventurers during the event, they will not join you after the event ends, regardless of their level or stats.<\/div><div>5. If a temporary adventurer permanently joins your roster, you will be able to read their Adventurer Story.<\/div><div>6. You will not be able to use blazons, emblems, or otherworld fragments obtained in this event in future events.<\/div><div>7. For details concerning this raid event, check the Help section on the raid event&rsquo;s top page in the game.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1567231200,"prev_article_id":"670","next_article_id":"713","image_path":"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/3ad4f173f770e116f48150d16e3aa279.png","update_time":1569478542}}}'